quiz.name: Pre Assessment
quiz.intro:
Hello folks,

This assessment needs to be completed before starting the course. It will take only couple of minutes to do so!

Warmly,

Team Llama

feedback.feedbacktext: Well done, you’re very self-aware!
You’re mostly self-aware, with a few areas you can develop.
You have some self-awareness, but there’s definitely room for improvement.
You’re lacking self-awareness... but you can learn!

question_attempt.questionsummary:
Can you name the behaviours that you are doing at all times?
: Yes, I’m always intentional with my behaviors and can name what I’m taking part
in at all times. ; No, I rarely am aware of what my body or mind is doing.
; Sometimes. I’m usually aware of what I’m doing, although at times, I get caught
up in something or don’t realize what I’m doing.
question_attempt.rightanswer:
Yes, I’m always intentional with my behaviors and can name what I’m taking part
in at all times.
question_attempt.responsesummary:
Yes, I’m always intentional with my behaviors and can name what I’m taking part
in at all times.

question_attempt.questionsummary:
Can you name the emotions that you are feeling at all times?
: Yes, I can always identify and name the emotion I’m feeling at any given moment.
; Sometimes. I’m usually aware of what emotion I’m feeling. However, it takes me a
few moments to recognize it, and strong emotions sometimes catch me off-guard. ; No, I rarely think about what emotion I’m feeling. I just feel something and act
accordingly.
question_attempt.rightanswer: Yes, I can always identify and name the emotion I’m feeling at any given moment.
question_attempt.responsesummary:
No, I rarely think about what emotion I’m feeling. I just feel something and act
accordingly.

question_attempt.questionsummary:
Can you identify what causes a shift to negative emotions?
: Sometimes. I can usually identify what caused a shift in emotions, although it
takes a little while for me to catch on. ; No, I rarely know what specifically causes me to shift to negative emotions. All of a
sudden, I’m no longer happy and I don’t know why. ; Yes, I can always identify what causes me to shift to negative emotions, whether it
be an event, person, or recurring trigger.
question_attempt.rightanswer:
Yes, I can always identify what causes me to shift to negative emotions, whether it
be an event, person, or recurring trigger.

question_attempt.questionsummary:
Can you name the emotional patterns you experience the most?
: Yes, I can list my standard emotional patterns right now, including what they are,
what causes them, and what effect they have on my life. ; No, I have no idea what emotional patterns I repeat. I have emotions, but I can’t
name any trends with when or why they happen. ; Somewhat. I generally know what I have a tendency to do, but it’s not always
consistent or recognizable.
question_attempt.rightanswer:
Yes, I can list my standard emotional patterns right now, including what they are,
what causes them, and what effect they have on my life.
question_attempt.responsesummary:
Yes, I can list my standard emotional patterns right now, including what they are,
what causes them, and what effect they have on my life.

question_attempt.questionsummary:
Can you name your deepest fear triggers?
: Somewhat. I can tell you what I’m most scared of, but I don’t fully know how it
affects my life and daily actions. ; No, I have no idea what a fear trigger even is or if I have one.
; Yes, I’m aware of my deepest fears and what triggers these fears in my everyday
life. I understand how pervasive these fears are in my thoughts and actions.
question_attempt.rightanswer:
Yes, I’m aware of my deepest fears and what triggers these fears in my everyday
life. I understand how pervasive these fears are in my thoughts and actions.
question_attempt.responsesummary:
Yes, I’m aware of my deepest fears and what triggers these fears in my everyday
life. I understand how pervasive these fears are in my thoughts and actions.

: Somewhat. I can tell you what I’m most ashamed of, but I don’t fully know how it

in my everyday life. I understand how pervasive this shame is in my thoughts and
actions. ; No, I have no idea what a shame trigger even is or if I have one.
question_attempt.rightanswer:
Yes, I know the things that give me the most shame and what triggers this shame
in my everyday life. I understand how pervasive this shame is in my thoughts and
actions.
question_attempt.responsesummary:
Yes, I know the things that give me the most shame and what triggers this shame

question_attempt.questionsummary:
Can you name the principles and values you believe in the most?
: Somewhat. I can name a few principles and qualities that are most important to
me, but I haven’t given this list a lot of thought. ; Yes, I can list my guiding principles and core values right now. I know how to
distinguish between what I care about and the outside influence of others. ; No, I have no idea what values I personally believe in the most.
question_attempt.rightanswer:
Yes, I can list my guiding principles and core values right now. I know how to
distinguish between what I care about and the outside influence of others.
question_attempt.responsesummary:
Yes, I can list my guiding principles and core values right now. I know how to
distinguish between what I care about and the outside influence of others.

question_attempt.questionsummary:
How much do you consider these principles when making decisions? : A lot. Not only do I know what these principles are, but I design my life and
decision-making around them. They give clarity to my decisions. ; Somewhat. I know what my principles are but don’t really know when they come
into effect in my life. ; Not at all. I live my life without ever giving a thought to any principles.
question_attempt.rightanswer:
A lot. Not only do I know what these principles are, but I design my life and
decision-making around them. They give clarity to my decisions.
question_attempt.responsesummary: Not at all. I live my life without ever giving a thought to any principles.

question_attempt.questionsummary:
Can you name the passions that you have and lose track of time while doing? : No, I don’t have any clear passions.
; Somewhat. I can list things that I enjoy doing, although I wouldn’t necessarily call
them passions. ; Yes, I know what I’m passionate about and why they give me joy.
question_attempt.rightanswer: Yes, I know what I’m passionate about and why they give me joy.
question_attempt.responsesummary: Yes, I know what I’m passionate about and why they give me joy.

question_attempt.questionsummary:
Can you state a list of goals and ambitions you have for yourself?
: No, I don’t really have any driving goals or ambitions in my life.
; Somewhat. I have a few goals and ambitions, although they might not be the most
defined. ; Yes, I can state a list of goals right now that include both short-term and long-term
goals. I understand what I want out of life and can express these ambitions.
question_attempt.rightanswer:
Yes, I can state a list of goals right now that include both short-term and long-term
goals. I understand what I want out of life and can express these ambitions.
question_attempt.responsesummary:
Yes, I can state a list of goals right now that include both short-term and long-term

question_attempt.questionsummary:
Can you describe the environment you thrive in the most?
: Yes, I can describe the ideal environment that I need to be happy and be
successful, including the pace, energy, and structure that I thrive in. ; No, I don’t know what environment works best for me. I just try to make it work
; Somewhat. I know certain things that I would want, but I can’t fully describe the
exact environment that I thrive in.
question_attempt.rightanswer:
Yes, I can describe the ideal environment that I need to be happy and be
successful, including the pace, energy, and structure that I thrive in.
question_attempt.responsesummary:
Somewhat. I know certain things that I would want, but I can’t fully describe the
exact environment that I thrive in.
